quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,217,"And rely upon the Exalted in Might, the Merciful,"
  26,218,"Who sees you when you arise{1}",footnotes:1:From your bed at night for prayer while you are alone.
  26,219,"And your movement among those who prostrate.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., among those who pray with you in congregation.
  33,70,"O you who have believed, fear Allāh and speak words of appropriate justice."
  33,71,"He will [then] amend for you your deeds and forgive you your sins. And whoever obeys Allāh and His Messenger has certainly attained a great attainment."
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the Trust{1} to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, and they declined to bear it and feared it; but man [undertook to] bear it. Indeed, he was unjust and ignorant.{2}",footnotes:1:The acceptance of obligations and obedience to Allāh.Coveting its reward while forgetting the penalty for failure to keep his commitment.
  34,49,"Say, ",footnotes:1:This expression alludes to complete inability, meaning that falsehood was abolished.
  34,50,"Say, "
  34,51,"And if you could see{1} when they are terrified but there is no escape, and they will be seized from a place nearby.",footnotes:1:i.e., have a glimpse of the Hereafter.
  35,34,"And they will say, "
  35,35,"He who has settled us in the home of duration [i.e., Paradise] out of His bounty. There touches us not in it any fatigue, and there touches us not in it weariness [of mind]."
  35,36,"And for those who disbelieve will be the fire of Hell. [Death] is not decreed for them{1} so they may die, nor will its torment be lightened for them. Thus do We recompense every ungrateful one.",footnotes:1:Or "They are not killed."
  36,19,"They said, ",footnotes:1:Your threat against us.
  36,20,"And there came from the farthest end of the city a man, running. He said, "
  36,21,"Follow those who do not ask of you [any] payment, and they are [rightly] guided."
  37,4,"Indeed, your God is One,"
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and that between them and Lord of the sunrises.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., each point or place of sunrise.
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the nearest heaven with an adornment of stars"